This paper discusses the use of social media in scholarly communication, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as the paper focuses on the use of social media metrics as indicators of scientific impact. The sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also highly relevant, as the paper discusses the use of social media platforms for scholarly communication. The sub-categories cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) are also relevant, as the paper touches on issues related to data reliability, validity, and the impact of social media on academia and society.
